parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction of the hybrid system can cause the vehicle to lose power, leading to a loss of control, which can increase the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The vehicle suddenly loses power
the engine warning light comes on
the vehicle's speed suddenly reduces
the vehicle is unable to maintain speed
the vehicle's electric motor turns off and the gas motor does not immediately turn on.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction of the voltage indicator can cause the vehicle's electrical system to malfunction, leading to a loss of power, which can increase the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The voltage indicator switches from normal voltage to high voltage
the vehicle's electrical system malfunctions.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the vehicle to turn off completely can cause the vehicle's electrical system to remain active, leading to a risk of fire or electrical shock.
symptoms: The vehicle will not turn off completely
the engine still revs after the vehicle is turned off.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The manufacturer's failure to service the electrical loss recall can cause the vehicle's electrical system to malfunction, leading to a loss of power, which can increase the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The manufacturer refuses to service the electrical loss recall
the vehicle's electrical system malfunctions.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Engine Failure Due to Oil Drain Bolt Issue
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The engine failure can cause the vehicle to stall or lose power, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded. The lack of oil in the engine can also cause significant damage to the engine, leading to costly repairs.
symptoms: The dashboard displays a warning message to turn off the car
the engine loses power
the vehicle stalls
the oil drain bolt is loose or missing
the oil level is low or empty.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Transmission Error and Hybrid System Malfunction
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The transmission error and hybrid system malfunction can cause the vehicle to lose power, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded. The error can also cause the vehicle to become stuck in electric mode, making it difficult to drive.
symptoms: The vehicle gets stuck in electric mode
the transmission error message appears on the dashboard
the vehicle loses power
the vehicle must be turned off and on to reset
the error message says "Service Immediately".

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the rearview camera system can reduce the driver's visibility while reversing, increasing the risk of accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The rearview camera activates but displays a previous image instead of the current image behind the vehicle
the display screen fails to display the current image behind the vehicle
the rearview camera system does not function properly.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction of the infotainment system can distract the driver and cause accidents, as well as reduce the functionality of safety features such as the rearview camera.
symptoms: The infotainment system displays incorrect or outdated information
the system freezes or becomes unresponsive
the system fails to display critical safety information such as the rearview camera feed.
